completion: I have always been infatuated with hair and want to be in a position to help people feel confident and express that in their personal style. I hope to start my career working in a salon to get a few years of experience and build my client network. I absolutely love to travel and it would be a dream to be involved in fashion weeks all around the world. I also hope that though out my career I can give back to the community with free hair cuts for the less fortunate and any other ways I can help, armed with a cape and my shears. I think special effects make-up is so cool and I would love to further my education with the 100 hour make-up course. I think working in special effects make-up would be an amazing outlet for me to express my creativity and my passion for this industry. When I was first out of highschool I didn't know which path to take. I had always talked about going to cosmetology school but i was discouraged by my parents. So, because of my mom's wishes, I got my pharmacy technician certification instead. While it was a big accomplishment for me I wasn't happy doing that kind of work. I quit my job at CVS and headed to the west coast by truck. I made it to Eugene Oregon where I lived for three years before coming here to Salt Lake City. Although I wish I had pursued my career in cosmetology a lot sooner in life, I believe that everything happens for a reason, and I am beyond grateful and excited to begin my education at The Paul Mitchell School.
